  • Method Details

    • promptCSV

      public static VotingSystem promptCSV()
      This function will prompt the user for the name of the CSV containing the election information. It will then read in the first line of the file and create a new instance of OPLElection, IRElection, or POElection based on that line. Once this instance has been created, the class variables csvName, csvFile, and electionType will be set
      Returns:
      sys A VotingSystem instance with csvName, csvFile, and electionType set

    • promptAudit

      public void promptAudit()
      This function will prompt the user for the desired audit file name. If one is not provided, the function will generate a unique name. It will then create the file and open it for writing. It then sets the class variable auditFile to the PrintWriter to be accessed and written to throughout the algorithm.

    • promptMedia

      public void promptMedia()
      This function will prompt the user for the desired media file name. If one is not provided, the function will generate a unique name. It will then create the file and open it for writing. It then sets the class variable mediaFile to the PrintScanner to be accessed and written to throughout the algorithm.

    • coinToss

      public int coinToss​(int numTied)
      Break any ties throughout either algorithm. It takes in the number of candidates involved in the tie, and returns an integer representing the losing candidate. It will simulate 1000 coin tosses and take the 1001 result to ensure randomness.
      Parameters:
      numTied - an int, the number of objects with the same values
      Returns:
      option an int, the chosen
